What are the odds of rolling an 8?

The Answer

13.89%

or exactly 5/36

When rolling two standard six-sided dice, an 8 is the second most likely outcome (tied with 6), beaten only by 7. Let's explore why.

grid_view The Probability Space

There are 36 total combinations when rolling two dice (6 sides 6 sides).

To get a sum of 8, the dice must land on one of these 5 pairs:

  • Die 1: 2, Die 2: 6 Sum: 8
  • Die 1: 3, Die 2: 5 Sum: 8
  • Die 1: 4, Die 2: 4 Sum: 8
  • Die 1: 5, Die 2: 3 Sum: 8
  • Die 1: 6, Die 2: 2 Sum: 8

Why is 7 more likely?

To roll a 7, you have 6 combinations (1+6, 2+5, 3+4, 4+3, 5+2, 6+1). This is one more combination than 8 has.

Probability of 7 6/36 (16.67%)

Why are 2 and 12 rare?

There is only 1 way to roll a 2 (1+1) and only 1 way to roll a 12 (6+6).

Probability of 2 1/36 (2.78%)
